reviews.text: The experience here was amazing! Oysters was very fresh and lots of sea food to choose. We are friend gathering of 7 people and Deepak made our night even more interesting by greetings us with the drinks. Definitely wanna come back again and I will miss the food here

Fantastic buffeet! Great selection, tasty lobster, great tuna sashimi, beef. Very good service, amazing view if you book early and get a window table. Modern decor. In overall truly great experience, definitely would recommend.

Came here for dinner buffet, the food was below average specially the seafood. Lobster and prawns were absolutely tasteless and felt like 2 days old. Clams were full of sand.The only edible food was the roast beef and the parma ham with melon. One surprisingly good thing was the ice lemon tea which tasted very good for a hotel.Overall the service was good but it could not compensate the bad quality and poor variations of food.
Food are generally good. But as an adult not teenager, you don’t have the stomach for much food.

Came here for the Sunday brunch, it is phenomenal. Highly enjoyed everything they served up, from the oysters and clams, to the various sashimi options, and cuts of meat.
Definitely worth an indulgent visit, just be ready to not be very productive the rest of the day.
The accompanying champagne is excellent, along with other cocktails like bloody mary’s and gin and tonics.
Finally all the desserts were fantastic.
This is a great way to spend a Sunday and about 990 HKD (with SC added), about US$120 pp.
